input:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant BaldEagle : obj
constant Cat : obj
constant Squirrel : obj
constant Bear : obj

constant Chases : obj → obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Visits : obj → obj → Prop
constant Kind : obj → Prop
constant Sees : obj → obj → Prop
constant Blue : obj → Prop
constant Cold : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Chases BaldEagle Cat
axiom T2 : Chases BaldEagle Squirrel
axiom T3 : Round BaldEagle
axiom T4 : Visits BaldEagle Squirrel
axiom T5 : Kind Bear
axiom T6 : Sees Bear BaldEagle
axiom T7 : Blue Cat
axiom T8 : Sees Cat Bear
axiom T9 : Visits Cat BaldEagle
axiom T10 : Visits Cat Squirrel
axiom T11 : Chases Squirrel Bear
axiom T12 : Visits Squirrel BaldEagle

axiom R1 : Sees Cat BaldEagle ∧ Sees Cat Bear → Kind BaldEagle
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Visits x Cat → Chases Cat Squirrel
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Bear → Sees x Cat
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Cat → Sees Cat BaldEagle
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Bear ∧ Cold Bear → Chases Bear BaldEagle
axiom R6 : Blue Cat → Cold Cat
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Kind x → Sees x Bear
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Visits x Squirrel ∧ Chases x Cat → Chases Cat Bear
axiom R9 : ∀ x : obj, Kind x → Chases x BaldEagle

theorem bald_eagle_sees_cat : Sees BaldEagle Cat :=
begin
  sorry,
end
output:
theorem bald_eagle_sees_cat : Sees BaldEagle Cat :=
begin
  apply R4,
  apply R3,
  apply R7,
  apply R1,
  split,
  exact T9,
  exact T8,
end

-- The answer is True
